article.headline: Indiana St. 59, Tulane 47
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Gabe Moore scored 15 points and grabbed four rebounds to lead Indiana State to a 59-47 victory over Tulane on Saturday. Moore shot just 3-of-12 from the floor but hit 8-of-8 free throws as the Sycamores (3-1) shot 19-of-26 (73 percent) from the line. Indiana State led 27-25 at halftime despite shooting only 9-of-31 (29 percent) from the floor in the first half. David Gomez led Tulane (4-2) with a game-high 20 points on 9-of-13 shooting. A 3-pointer by Marico Stinson gave the Sycamores a 43-42 lead midway through the second half and set off a 19-5 run over the final 7:37. Stinson finished 3-of-5 from 3-point range. Indiana State outrebounded Tulane 43-32 but was outscored in the paint 34-18.
